text: Somogy is an administrative county in Hungary. The capital of Somogy county is Kaposvár. It is in the southwestern part of the country. It borders with the Croatian counties of Koprivnica-Križevci and Virovitica-Podravina and the Hungarian counties of Baranya, Fejér, Tolna, Veszprém and Zala. In 2019, 301,429 people lived there. Its area is 6,065 km². Category:Counties of Hungary
title: Somogy County
